cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.EM, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category as the paper investigates the fundamental limits of information transmission in wireless communication system with RF-based energy harvesting. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of the proposed system in sensor networks and body-area networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible sub-category as the paper considers the joint investigation of two-way information transmission between two nodes under an external power supply constraint. 
4. cs.EM (Electromagnetics) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with RF-based energy harvesting, which involves electromagnetic waves. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper discusses the transmission strategy for a master node and child node in a wireless communication system.
